@Nancy 

It would seem to me that an alarm might be a necessity for waking up, but not for retiring.  But once I retired eight years ago, I stopped worrying about setting alarms except when I had something exciting, like getting to the airport, to do.

My 92-year-old mother-in-law, retired now for 25 years, still sets an alarm every morning.  To take her medicines, she says.  I take mine when I wake up.  I like my way better.

